  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd - \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0b95 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ready to help Sri Lankans affected by the crisis - British Foreign Office",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "British Foreign Office Minister Vicky Ford has said that she is closely monitoring Sri Lanka's economic situation, including foreign exchange data published by the government and the Central Bank.",
        "In a letter to the British public, Minister Vicky Ford noted that tourism was Sri Lanka's main source of income, earning about 30 percent of its revenue prior to the spread of the corona virus.",
        "However, Sri Lanka's tourism industry, which fell by about 80 percent in 2020, will fall by 60 percent in 2021.",
        "Britain is a major contributor to the country's tourism industry. Sri Lanka has been one of the top three suppliers of raw materials to Sri Lanka for the past three years, according to British Foreign Secretary Vicky Ford.",
        "Over the past three years, remittances from Sri Lankans working abroad have made a significant contribution to the Sri Lankan economy and accounted for 8 and 9 percent of Sri Lanka's GDP in 2019 and 2020, respectively.",
        "However, he pointed out that remittances from Sri Lankans working abroad have fallen by 20 per cent by 2021, the highest level since 2011.",
        "In this context, Prime Minister Vicky Ford on May 30 welcomed Prime Minister Vicky Ford to Sri Lanka on May 30 to acknowledge that Sri Lanka is facing a major economic crisis and to welcome in-depth discussions with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) on the need for restructuring to bring the economy back on track. He reiterated his commitment to help the people of Sri Lanka."
      ],
